│ `i1` is a bit tricky for signed comparisons. In LLVM, `i1` is often treated as an unsigned 1-bit integer. However, for signed operations, the MSB is the sign bit. For `i1`, the single  │
│ bit is the MSB.                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ - `i1 0`: sign bit is 0 (positive).                                                                                                                                                      │
│ - `i1 1`: sign bit is 1 (negative).                                                                                                                                                      │
│ The `samesign` predicate requires both operands to have the same sign. Since `i1 0` is positive and `i1 1` is negative, their signs are different. When the signs are different, the     │
│ result of `icmp samesign` is `poison`.                                                                                                                                                   │
